'Your skills are renowned, [placeholder], and tales of your bravery and daring have spread unchecked far and wide. Good people everywhere cheer your name and speak of the evils you have fought and over which you have triumphed.

'Few indeed have overcome the challenges you have bested, and few have earned your reputation for bravery. One such champion is Gwesgylliel, an Elf-maiden known for both her beauty and the swiftness of her blades. She surely has words for a champion such as you, and you would be wise to heed them.

'Gwesgylliel has gone to the glade of Lin Giliath, in Meluinen in the North Downs, to aid her people in its defence. She will surely wish to speak with a champion of your stature.'
